turn-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3614437\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 11, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104lso1665702640824.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lso1665702640824.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lso1665702640824.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"lso1665702640824\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Tab Width (TabWidth)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Width of all tabs in the widget, in character cells. By default, the tab size is based\n    on the length of the longest label,or the size of the default image. Value is a number; minimum\n    is <code class=\"ph codeph\">5</code> characters. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lso1665702640824__p_d107861e1_d107862e1_d107863e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code>TabWidth<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">Number</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code></p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lso1665702640824__section_dkb_412_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d986968e65\">Usage</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"lso1665702640824__table_d12707e1_d12708e1_d12709e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Dynamic? </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Yes </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Supported in Grid? </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> No </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Dependencies: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Ignored if <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Justify</span> is\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code>. <p class=\"p\">Overrides the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Fixed Tab\n                  Width</span>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lso1665702640824__section_d4q_s12_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d986968e123\">Using in ProcScript</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lso1665702640824__p_d107870e1_d107871e1_d107872e1\">You can use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$properties</span> or\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldproperties</span> to set or get the property and its value. For more\n        information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zie1665702558978.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zie1665702558978.html\" title=\"Return or set the current widget properties of a field.\">$properties</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aud1705998763272.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aud1705998763272.html\" title=\"Return or set the current widget properties of an instance of a field.\">$fieldproperties</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"lso1665702640824__pre_g2s_t12_1xb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$fieldproperties(FLD) = \"tabwidth=10\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lso1665702640824__section_bhv_t12_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d986968e155\">Applies To</h2>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gyf1688451219719.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gyf1688451219719.html\" title=\"The utabex widget enables users to navigate through a collection of contained forms by clicking a tab to display the form. The utabex widget is highly customizable, allowing extensive control over the appearance and behavior of the tabs. Uniface provides a logical widget called TabEx, which is mapped to utabex.\">utabex (TabEx)</a></p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/raq1665702640601.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Fixed Tab Width (FixedWidth)</a><p>Determines whether the biggest label in tab set defines the tab size used for all tabs, or the tab size varies with its label.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nym1665702640684.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Justified (Justify)</a><p>Justifies the tabs so that they occupy the full width of the tab widget. Default is False.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614437\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614437\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Tab Width (TabWidth) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 11, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Tab Width (TabWidth) Width of all tabs in the widget, in character cells. By default, the tab size is based on the length of the longest label,or the size of the default image. Value is a number; minimum is 5 characters. \" TabWidth = Number \" Usage Dynamic? Yes Supported in Grid? No Dependencies: Ignored if Justify is True . Overrides the Fixed Tab Width . Using in ProcScript You can use $properties or $fieldproperties to set or get the property and its value. For more information, see $properties and $fieldproperties . $fieldproperties(FLD) = \"tabwidth=10\" Copy Applies To utabex (TabEx) Related Links Fixed Tab Width (FixedWidth) Determines whether the biggest label in tab set defines the tab size used for all tabs, or the tab size varies with its label. Justified (Justify) Justifies the tabs so that they occupy the full width of the tab widget. Default is False. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}